articles.author: Jarrett Renshaw, Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden will meet with Japan and South Korea's leaders on Friday as they seek to preserve their diplomatic progress ahead of a new Trump administration that many fear could upend alliances worldwide.
articles.title: Biden to meet South Korea, Japan leaders for pre-Trump huddle on risk

articles.author: Maya Gebeily
articles.description: An Israeli airstrike flattened a building near one of the busiest traffic junctions in the Lebanese capital.
articles.title: Israel hits Beirut suburb after US delivers truce proposal

articles.author: Marvin Valladares
articles.description: Wading through waist-deep water, residents along the northern coast of Honduras trudged through the streets on Friday carrying their belongings and pets, as heavy rains from Tropical Storm Sara caused widespread flooding across the area.
articles.title: Honduras battles flooding as Tropical Storm Sara unleashes heavy rainfall
Xi tells Ishiba China hopes Japan will 'properly handle' history, Taiwan issues

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A Nations League match between Romania and Kosovo in Bucharest was abandoned in stoppage time on Friday after the visiting players walked off the field when they heard pro-Serbia chanting from the home fans.
articles.title: Kosovo-Romania match abandoned after players walk off pitch following pro-Serbia chants

articles.author: Lucy Papachristou, Filipp Lebedev, Mark Trevelyan
articles.description: Protesters stormed the parliament of the Russian-backed breakaway Georgian region of Abkhazia on Friday and demanded the resignation of its leader over an unpopular investment agreement with Moscow.
articles.title: Protesters demand leader's ouster in Russian-backed breakaway region of Georgia

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Argentine police arrested a man in Buenos Aires who possessed a large number of vintage Nazi weapons decorated with Third Reich symbols from Adolf Hitler's infamous regime, officials said on Friday.
articles.title: Argentina seizes large arsenal of Nazi weapons, Hitler-era memorabilia

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China is willing to be partners and friends with the United States, China's ambassador to Washington said, seeking to strengthen dialogue between the world's two largest economies.
articles.title: China willing to be partners, friends with US, Chinese envoy says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thailand arrested 70 illegal immigrants including 30 children suspected to be Rohingya from Myanmar on an island in the country's south, Thai official said on Saturday, in the latest wave of arrivals to Southeast Asia.
articles.title: Thailand detains 70 illegal migrants believed to be Rohingya from Myanmar

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The defence ministers of Australia, Japan and the United States will meet in the Australian city of Darwin on Sunday to discuss continued military cooperation, Australia's Defence Minister Richard Marles said on Saturday.
articles.title: Australia, US, Japan to hold defence trilateral in Darwin on Sunday
